'''István Borzsák''' (24 December 1914, [[Monor]] - 9 December 2007, Budapest), was a Hungarian [[classical scholar]]<ref name=Rtt>Rttook, Zsigmund. (1997) [http://epa.niif.hu/01400/01462/00020/pdf/005-015.pdf "The contribution of Hungary to international classical scholarship"], ''[[Hungarian Studies (journal)|Hungarian Studies]]'', 12. Retrieved 12 March 2014. [https://www.webcitation.org/6NtepxQmg Archived here.]</ref> who was a specialist in [[Roman literature]]. He was a member of the [[Hungarian Academy of Sciences]].

==Selected publications==
*''Budai Ézsaiás és klasszika-filológiánk kezdetei'', Akadémiai Kiadó, Budapest, 1955.
*''P. Cornelius Tacitus, der Geschichtsschreiber'', A. Druckenmüller, Stuttgart, 1968.

